1. Access to the Highpointe Trails. The Association has established a trail system for the 
use and enjoyment of Owners and their authorized guests. 

2. USE OF THE TRAILS IS AT YOUR OWN RISK. The Association is not responsible for 
accidents, injuries or loss of personal property. The trails are unattended and feature 
natural terrain, features, vegetation, and wildlife. Owners and their guests use the trails 
at their own risk and are solely responsible for the safety and well-being of themselves, 
their guests, any minors under their supervision, and that of any designated childcare 
providers. 

3. Hours of Operation. The Management Staff and/or the Association may establish hours 
of operation for the Highpointe trails. 

4. Maintenance. The trail systems and/or surrounding areas may be closed for various 
periods of time to facilitate maintenance. 

5. Pets. All pets must be leashed at all times. Pet waste must be immediately removed. 

6. Prohibitions. The following are NOT permitted in the trail areas: 

a. Rough play; 

b. Excessive screaming; 



